    <h1>Cookies</h1>
    
    <p>When we provide services, we want to make them easy, useful and reliable. This sometimes involves placing small amounts of information on your computer. These include small files known as cookies. They cannot be used to identify you personally on this site.</p>

    <p>These pieces of information can be used to improve the service we provide to you by:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>remembering settings so you don't have to select them whenever you load a page</li>
      <li>remembering information you've given (e.g. your postcode) so you don't need to enter it several times</li>
      <li>measuring how you use the website so we can make sure it meets your needs</li>
    </ul>

    <p>You can manage these small files yourself and learn more about them from <a href="http://www.aboutcookies.org" title="Information about Cookies">AboutCookies.org</a>.</p>

    <hr/>

    <h2>How we use cookies</h2>
    
    <p>GOV.UK uses cookies in several places - we've listed each of them below with more details about why we use them and how long they will last.</p>
    
    <p>In most cases, we will let you know <strong>before</strong> we store a cookie on your computer by providing an icon similar to this: <span class="sets-cookie" style="background: #fde387; font-size: 0.8em; border: #bc9509; padding: 2px 3px; border-radius: 0.5em;"><a href="#" title="This link is an example that doesn't do anything">sets a cookie</a>.</span></p>
    

    
    <h3 id="analyticscookies">Measuring website usage (Google Analytics)</h3>
    <p>We use Google Analytics to collect analytics and information about how people use this site.  We do this to make sure it is meeting its usersâ€™ needs and understanding how we could do it better.</p>
    <p>Google Analytics stores information about what pages you visit, how long you are on the site, how you got here and what you click on. This information cannot be used to identify you and we do not allow Google to use our analytics data.</p>
    
    <p>The following cookies are set by Google Analytics:</p>
    
