    <hr/>
    
    <h3 id="tourcookies">Remembering if you've seen the GOV.UK introductory popup box</h3>
    <p>On your first visit to the GOV.UK beta website, you will see a popup box welcoming you to the website and providing background to the beta. When you close this box, we will store a cookie so that we know you have seen the popup and know not to show it to you again.</p>
    
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Typical Content</th>
          <th>Expires</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>govuktour</td>
          <td>The word 'dismiss' once you have closed the popup box.</td>
          <td>4 months <!-- currently 1 year --></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <h3 id="locationcookies">Storing your approximate location</h3>
    <p>Some parts of this website provides you with information related to your location.  For example, rather than providing a list of all <a href="/uk-online-centre-internet-access-computer-training" title="find UK Online Centres near you">UK Online Centres</a>, we just can usually direct you to the nearest one.</p>
    
    <p>When you enter your postcode we save it (and related information such as your longitude, latitude and a friendly name for the location) to a cookie.  Saving the information to a cookie means that you don't need to type in the postcode every time.</p>
    
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Typical Content</th>
          <th>Expires</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>govukgeo</td>
          <td>Details about your location (such as postcode, longitude/latitude and a 'friendly name' for where we think you are).</td>
          <td>4 months <!-- currently 1 month --></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <h3 id="usabilitycookies">Storing your usability settings</h3>
    <p>The GOV.UK website provides usability settings that can be switched on as required.  When these settings are turned on, we store this in a cookie so that we know to use these settings on every page you look at.</p>
    
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
